{
  "id": 5054329641893888,
  "name": "Renewed HTML insertion&streaming methods",
  "summary": "Expose multiple HTML setting methods that provide a coherent story for dynamically inserting markup into an existing document.\n\n- Positional methods (before/after/append/prepend/replaceWith) that take HTML as argument, effectively replacing insertAdjacentHTML.\n- Streaming methods (stream{Append}HTML{Unsafe}) which return a WritableStream\n- Passing {runScripts} as part of SetHTMLUnsafeOptions, mimicking createContextualFragment behavior.\n- Supporting createParserOptions in trusted types, allowing trusted types to override scripting mode and sanitizer.",
  "markdown_fields": [],
  "blink_components": [
    "Blink>HTML>Parser"
  ],
